<br>
I understand that mobs ENRAGE at 10% health for about 10 seconds, so depending on what kind of group I'm in, I try to time it so I don't get riposted when it's enraged.<br>
<br>
My last group had me (61 War), ~56 War, ~55 Dru, 60 Clr, 60 Enc, and ~55 Wiz camping Hobgobs. Very low dps, so I was the one trying to do the hit that made the gob enrage using a Reaver (2HS 40/40). <!--EZCODE BOLD START--><strong>What I do is duck</strong><!--EZCODE BOLD END-->. It turns off auto attack and if I riposte one of the mob's attacks, I don't attack back. I don't taunt or disarm, but I beg, since I want to improve my skill. It worked out surprisingly well. <p><!--EZCODE FONT START--><span style="font-family:Verdana;"><!--EZCODE LINK START--><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=560604" target="top"><!--EZCODE BOLD START--><strong>Drackoz Darkstar</strong><!--EZCODE BOLD END--></a><!--EZCODE LINK END--> - 64 Barbarian Shaman<br>
